                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> The egarhowl rolls initiative</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> At the start of combat, an inverted, reversed explosion of spiritual and void energy implodes in a @Template[type:emanation|distance:30] centered on the egarhowlâ€”a reversal of the creature's spiritually explosive death. All creatures in the area take @Damage[6d8[spirit]] damage (@Check[fortitude|dc:35|basic] save); creatures that fail this save are also @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1} for 1 round as time seems to distort around them.</p>"
                },
